  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison discusses plans to go to Vermont with Oliver Johnson. He is glad that &quot;the subscription list of the Standard more than holds its own in these desperate times.&quot; The receipts for the Liberator are $600-$800 less than usual. He hears that Fanny Garrison is planning to return home. William L. Garrison is apalled by the war and exclaims: &quot;What a war! what slaughter! what retribution for our national transgression! and what little progress in putting down the rebellion! I have no more faith in McClellan than before.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Accompanied by an envelope with the delivery address: Editor of the A. S. Standard, 48 Beekman Street, New York City, N. Y.</subfield>
